          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <placeName>Charleston</placeName>
                                        <date>Jany 18<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1851</date>
                              </p>
                              <p><addressee>Revd I. Leeser</addressee>. Dr Sir. I have at<lb/> last
                                        collected the amt due by <persName>I. I
                                        Cohen</persName>,<lb/> and take pleasure in remitting Ck
                                        for<lb/> $27.00 in full for the 3 subscriptions before<lb/>
                                        alluded to. I begin to despair of <persName>Lewis<lb/>
                                                  Levy</persName>, and would suggest that you write
                                        him<lb/> a few lines requesting him to remit <hi
                                                  rend="underline">me</hi><lb/> the amt of his dues,
                                        as you have no agt<lb/> in <placeName>Augusta</placeName>,
                                        and are anxious to collect all<lb/> outstanding debts. I can
                                        see no other chance<lb/> of inducing him to make paymt.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Yr list has not increased much since<lb/> I last
                                        wrote you, owing perhaps to want of<lb/> energy on my part.
                                        I have been too busy to<lb/> bestow upon it the requisite
                                        attention. Hereafter<lb/> I shall do better I hope. Mother
                                        sends her<lb/> kind regards as do all of our family &amp;<lb/>
                                        <persName>Aunts P &amp; R</persName> hope that you may
                                        be<lb/> enabled to pay <placeName>Charleston</placeName> a
                                        visit this<lb/> winter. We have here, a <persName>Mr E
                                                  Hart</persName> of yr<lb/> city, Brother of
                                                  <persName>Mr A Hart</persName>. He has recd<lb/>
                                        some attention and appears to be a very<lb/> worthy young
                                        man. <persName>Miss Isabel Moses</persName><lb/> has
                                        returned to <placeName>Columbus</placeName>, having
                                        heard<lb/> of the sudden death of her Sisters child,<lb/>
                                        The <persName>Jenny Lind</persName> excitement drew a<lb/>
                                        number of strangers to the city and made<lb/> our streets
                                        gay and lively for some time.</p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>It is supposed that <persName>Mr Joshua Lazarus</persName>
                                        will<lb/> be elected to the vacant Presidency of our<lb/>
                                        congregation. <persName>Mr I
                                                  Ottolengri<add>?</add></persName> has just been
                                        made<lb/> Trustee. <persName>Rev Mr Rosenfeldt</persName>
                                        has a call<lb/> from <placeName>California</placeName> which
                                        he intends to accept<lb/> &amp; will leave for that region,
                                        I am informed)<lb/> in a few weeks. His salary is to be
                                        $4000<lb/> pr annum, which appears munificent<lb/> when
                                        contrasted with the <hi rend="underline">very
                                        liberal</hi><lb/> provisions yr congregation made for
                                        you<lb/> during yr ministration.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">We have not recd our number of the<lb/> Occident
                                        for <date>Jany</date>, altho most of yr. Chas<lb/>
                                        subscribers have theirs. Can you, without<lb/> inconvenience
                                                  forw<hi rend="underline">d</hi>
                                        <persName>Mosher</persName> a duplicate<lb/> copy? I have
                                        read yr address, however<lb/> which cannot, I am sure,
                                        produce other<lb/> than a very favorable impression.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">You may be assured that the Editor of<lb/> the
                                        Asmonean is viewed in his true colors<lb/> by our community,
                                        and that his assaults<lb/> upon you, have a reactionary
                                        effect</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">You have doubtless heard that some<lb/> difference
                                        has arisen between <persName>Dr Eckman</persName><lb/> &amp;
                                                  <persName>Mr Posnanski</persName> produced by
                                        excited<lb/> controversial <sic>disenssions</sic>, and
                                        this<lb/> difference has been enlarged and<lb/> aggravated
                                        by the friends of either</p>
                              <pb n="3"/>
                              <p>gentleman who have taken up for one or<lb/> the other respectively.
                                        An attempt has been<lb/> and will be made, I fear, to bring
                                        the<lb/> matter before the congregation in which<lb/> the
                                        friends of <persName>mr P</persName> have a numerical<lb/>
                                        majority. His opinions however are not<lb/> held in
                                        reverence <hi rend="underline">now</hi>, by what I
                                        consider<lb/> the best and most intelligent portion of<lb/>
                                        our members. These last, will sustain <persName>Dr<lb/>
                                                  Eckman</persName> who is independent, and
                                        inclined<lb/> to orthodoxy.  </p>
                              <p rend="indent(9)">Yrs very Respflly</p>
                              <p rend="indent(9)">
                                        <persName role="author">T. J. Moise</persName>
                              </p>
                              <pb n="4"/>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Rev I. Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                        <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">
